20his%20wife's%20retirement%20account%20made%20the%20trades%20and%20that%20they%20didn't%20affect%20his%20judgment.%20He%20later%20filed%20a%20disclosure%20statement%20in%20the%20court%20record.%20The%20appeals%20court%20said%20that%20wasn't%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20delayed%20disclosure%2C%20taken%20together%20with%20the%20district%20court's%20consistent%20rulings%20in%20Boeing's%20favor%20during%20and%20after%20trial%2C%20could%20give%20an%20objective%20observer%20reason%20to%20question%20the%20district%20judge's%20impartiality%20in%20further%20proceedings%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20decision%2C%20which%20was%20posted%20Thursday%20by%20the%20US%20Court%20of%20Appeals%20for%20the%20Ninth%20Circuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJudicial%20ethics%20experts%20interviewed%20by%20Business%20Insider%20in%202024%20characterized%20Robart's%20trades%20and%20delayed%20disclosure%20to%20the%20parties%20as%20a%20minor%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZunum%20has%20been%20largely%20dormant%20since%20running%20out%20of%20money%20in%202019%2C%20which%20it%20blamed%20on%20Boeing%20stringing%20it%20along%20and%20sabotaging%20its%20efforts%20to%20obtain%20cash%20from%20other%20sources.%20Zunum%20had%20been%20developing%20a%20small%20hybrid-electric%20passenger%20plane%20that%20it%20planned%20to%20release%20in%202022%20and%20had%20planned%20to%20scale%20up%20to%20make%20and%20sell%20larger%20planes%20through%202030%2C%20it%20said%20in%20its%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJurors%20concluded%20last%20year%20that%20Boeing%20and%20its%20affiliate%20HorizonX%20had%20damaged%20Zunum%20by%20misappropriating%20its%20trade%20secrets%20and%20awarded%20%2472%20million.%20Based%20on%20previous%20filings%20that%20Zunum%20had%20broken%20agreements%20with%20HorizonX%2C%20the%20court%20also%20imposed%20a%20judgment%20for%20%249%20million%20plus%20interest%20against%20Zunum.%20That%20part%20of%20the%20decision%20survived%20Robart's%20ruling%20to%20void%20the%20%2472%20million%20verdict%20in%20favor%20of%20Zunum.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20appeals%20judges%20said%20Robart%20had%20overlooked%20%26quot%3Bsubstantial%26quot%3B%20evidence%20of%20Boeing's%20wrongdoing%20and%20Zunum's%20damages%20that%20the%20jury%20could%20have%20relied%20on.%20They%20said%20he%20had%20%26quot%3Bimpermissibly%20reweighed%20the%20evidence%20and%20failed%20to%20make%20all%20reasonable%20inferences%20in%20Zunum's%20favor.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20course%20of%20the%20past%20year%2C%20the%20two%20sides%20have%20been%20arguing%20in%20Robart's%20court%20about%20whether%20Zunum%20should%20have%20to%20sell%20its%20intellectual%20property%20to%20pay%20HorizonX.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZunum%20said%20its%20patents%20are%20hard%20to%20value%20and%20feared%20they%20would%20be%20sold%20at%20%26quot%3Bfire%20sale%26quot%3B%20prices.%20The%20company%20also%20said%20it%20has%20racked%20up%20about%20%2427%20million%20in%20legal%20fees%2C%20payable%20if%20it%20wins.%20Until%20its%20verdict%20was%20voided%2C%20its%20legal%20team%20at%20Holwell%20Shuster%20%26amp%3B%20Goldberg%20had%20argued%20that%20Boeing%20should%20be%20made%20to%20pay%20over%20%24160%20million%20because%20jurors%20found%20the%20aerospace%20giant's%20trade-secret%20theft%20had%20been%20%26quot%3Bwillful.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20Zunum%20and%20Boeing%20didn't%20immediately%20reply%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%20A%20clerk%20for%20Robart%20said%20he%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjudge-traded-boeing-stock-reversed-zunum-trade-secrets-appeal-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1755205487000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f1c804ce7f1785b2e929eb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjudge-traded-boeing-stock-reversed-zunum-trade-secrets-appeal-2025-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20struggling%20electric-pla