ific%20AI%20models%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20composite%20image%20of%20Sam%20Altman%20and%20the%20announcement%20of%20GPT-5%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689e0cb5194a2d49b8ae9227%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%20and%20his%20team%20have%20made%20changes%20to%20their%20GPT-5%20plans%20after%20user%20backlash.%3Cp%3EAP%2FGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EOpenAI%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-chatgpt-openai-ceo-career-net-worth-ycombinator-prepper-2023-1%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESam%20Altman%3C%2Fa%3E%20got%20a%20harsh%20lesson%20in%20how%20attached%20some%20users%20are%20to%20specific%20AI%20models.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAltman%20announced%20that%20OpenAI%20was%20bringing%20back%20access%20to%204o%20after%20an%20outcry%20on%20social%20media.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOpenAI's%20rough%20GPT-5%20rollout%20illustrates%20how%20sensitive%20changing%20AI%20models%20can%20be%20for%20some.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman's%20big%20GPT-5%20announcement%20was%20drowned%20out%20by%20users%20clamoring%20to%20keep%20their%20access%20to%20older%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELess%20than%2024%20hours%20after%20OpenAI%20announced%20it%20would%20discontinue%204o%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-sam-altman-model-rollout-explained-why-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAltman%20and%C2%A0his%20team%20signaled%20a%20retreat.%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0The%20fierce%20responses%20show%20that%20OpenAI's%20userbase%20has%20developed%20strong%20attachments%20to%20its%20various%20AI%20models%2C%20an%20achievement%20in%20and%20of%20itself%2C%20but%20one%20that%20poses%20a%20challenge%20to%20the%20company%20as%20it%20looks%20to%20convince%20people%20to%20shift%20to%20newer%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20been%20following%20the%20GPT-5%20rollout%2C%20one%20thing%20you%20might%20be%20noticing%20is%20how%20much%20of%20an%20attachment%20some%20people%20have%20to%20specific%20AI%20models%2C%26quot%3B%20Altman%20wrote%20on%20X%20on%20OpenAI%20Sunday.%20%26quot%3BIt%20feels%20different%20and%20stronger%20than%20the%20kinds%20of%20attachment%20people%20have%20had%20to%20previous%20kinds%20of%20technology%20(and%20so%20suddenly%20deprecating%20old%20models%20that%20users%20depended%20on%20in%20their%20workflows%20was%20a%20mistake).%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsers%20have%20molded%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChatGPTs%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20quasi-therapists%2C%20life%20coaches%2C%20and%20friends.%20Altman%20previously%20said%20that%20one%20user%20said%20their%20GPT%20gave%20them%20more%20encouragement%20than%20a%20parent%20ever%20had.%20Other%20tech%20companies%20have%20annoyed%20and%20angered%20their%20users%20by%20changing%20hardware%20or%20interface.%20But%20Altman's%20rival%20CEOs%20never%20dealt%20with%20emotional%20bonds%20that%20mimic%20real%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20personality%20changes%20between%20models%20were%20particularly%20jarring%20for%20some.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGPT5%20colder%20personality%20doesn't%20help%20either%2C%20it's%20just%20sad%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20user%20wrote%20during%20the%20Reddit%20AMA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20added%20after%20Altman%20said%20the%20older%20model%20was%20coming%20back%20for%20paid%20users%2C%20%26quot%3BThanks%2C%20Sam%E2%80%94bringing%20back%204o%20is%20a%20fantastic%20first%20step.%20Please%20consider%20keeping%20it%20around%20long-term.%20Many%20of%20us%20rely%20on%20it%20every%20day%2C%20not%20just%20for%20accuracy%20or%20logic%2C%20but%20for%20the%20warmth%20newer%20models%20sometimes%20miss.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENick%20Turley%2C%20OpenAI's%20head%20of%20ChatGPT%2C%20said%20that%20the%20Reddit%20comments%20showed%20%26quot%3Bjust%20how%20polarized%20users%20could%20be.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20just%20change%20that%20is%20difficult%20for%20folks%2C%20it's%20also%20the%20fact%20that%20people%20can%20have%20such%20a%20strong%20feeling%20about%20the%20personality%20of%20a%20model%2C%26quot%3B%20Turley%20told%20The%20Verge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENicole%20DiNicola%2C%20VP%20of%20Marketing%20at%20Smartcat%2C%20said%20one%20of%20the%20mistakes%20OpenAI%20made%20was%20abruptly%20removing%20access%20to%20earlier%20models%20without%20warning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20expectations%20have%20gotten%20so%20much%20higher%20for%20anything%20AI-related%20that%20it%20is%20much%20easier%20to%20be%20disappointed%2C%26quot%3B%20DiNicola%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETurley%20said%20the%20%26quot%3Blevel%20of%20passion%26quot%3B%20some%20users%20had%20for%204o%20led%20him%20to%20rethink%20some%20things.%20He%20also%20said%20that%20OpenAI%20announced%20before%20GPT-5%20that%20users%20could%20select%20from%20four%20personalities%20for%20their%20chatbots%3A%20cynic%2C%20robot%2C%20listener%2C%20and%20nerd.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20see%20people%20saying%2C%20'Hey%2C%20this%20is%20my%20only%20and%20best%20friend%2C'%20that%20doesn't%20feel%20like%20the%20type%20of%20thing%20that%20I%20wanted%20to%20build%20into%20ChatGPT.%26quot%3B%20Turley%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20feels%20like%20a%20side%20effect%2C%20and%20it's%20therefore%20worth%20taking%20seriously%20and%20studying%20closely%2C%20and%20that's%20what%20we're%20doing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarvey%20Hu%2C%20cofounder%20of%20General%20Agency%20AI%2C%20an%20applied%20research%20lab%2C%20said%20he%20found%20some%20of%20GPT-5's%20quick%20responses%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bslightly%20more%20stupid%20than%204o.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20functionality%20that%20can%20make%20users%20attached.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20may%20be%20a%20certain%20emotion%2C%20certain%20ways%20of%20prompting%20that%20you%20train%20yourself%20to%20learn%2C%20and%20if%20the%20certain%20model%20you%20got%20used%20gets%20sunsetted%20that%20could%20be%20definitely%20emotional%20thing%20for%20the%20users%2C%26quot%3B%20Hu%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgpt5-response-sam-altman-changes-4o-availability-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1755192661000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689e0fb8a17a8c5b4052e0ef%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgpt5-response-sam-altman-changes-4o-availability-2025-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22OpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%20said%20that%20he%20has%20taken%20notice%20of%20how%20attached%20some%20users%20have%20become%20to%20specific%20AI%20models.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22bgriffiths%40insider.com%20(Brent%20D.%20Griffiths)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A59%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgpt5-response-sam-altman-changes-4o-availability-2025-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Pavithra%20Menon%20questions%20Janhvi%20Kapoor's%20'Param%20Sundari'%20accent%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1755192536000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-123309744%2Cimgsize-38196.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fpavithra-menon-questions-janhvi-kapoors-param-sundari-accent-and-why-a-malayali-actor-wasnt-cast-hum-kam-talented-hote-hain-kya-%2Farticleshow%2F123309744.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F123309744.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EJanhvi%20Kapoor's%20upcoming%20film%2C%20Param%20S